net.sf.openrds   
 

Classes in net.sf.openrds used by net.sf.openrds
IMainNode
          Interface for the Main Node implementation.
A main node is responsible for distributing requisitions, controlling process nodes and load-balancing.
All requisitions to be processed must be passed to the main node, and never directly to a process node.
When the main node receives a new requisition, it will determine the best available node to process it and send the requistion for that node, to process it.
IndivisibleRequisition
          Represents a requisition to be processed on a single node.

INodeEventListener
          Interface for listening to node events.
IProcessNode
          Represents a node with the ability of processing a requisition on it's own process.
Node

NodeAlreadyExistsException
          This exception is thrown when trying to initialize a node that is already registered on the system.
NodeFactory
          This class can be used to help starting a main node and/or a process node, setting up a distributed system.

Requisition
